ef=\"#saving-and-loading\" aria-label=\"saving and loading permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Saving and Loading</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/6918/saving-and-loading-data-files#Item_1\">Using JSON</a> - Loading and saving manually via JSON.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Save-and-load-data-module-for-Gideros-Mobile\">DataSaver module</a> - User-friendly wrapper to make saving and loading data as easy as possible.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/5625/simple-savegame-encryption/p1\">Encrypting save files</a> - Some ideas (with code) about securing the save files from unwanted manipulation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"monetization\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#monetization\" aria-label=\"monetization permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Monetization</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/5801/tuto-video-tutorial-how-to-add-admob-plugin-to-your-app\">Admob integration</a> - Video tutorial about integrating Admob into your game.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/5806/tuto-video-tutorial-how-to-add-google-services-to-your-app\">Google Service integration</a> - Second part of the Admob tutorial showing Google Play Service integration.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"gui\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#gui\" aria-label=\"gui permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>GUI</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Nlcke/layout\">Layout</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Nlcke/layout\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8</span></span></a> - Comprehensive Gideors GUI framework (<a href=\"http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/6651/layout-gideros-gui-framework#Item_23\">forum entry</a>).</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Gideros-mobile-button-class\">Button class</a> - Simple class for creating clickable buttons.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Easy-input-for-choosing-packages-or-levels-in-Gideros-Mobile\">AceSlide class</a> - Sliding UI-Element that can be used for example for level selection.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"3d\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#3d\" aria-label=\"3d permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>3D</h3>\n<p><em>Note: 3D support is still in development but if you like to play around with it already, here are some starting points</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IfHwdJD6ad8\">Tutorial using 3D in Gideros</a> - Introduction by one of the maintainers of Gideros.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"plugins\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#plugins\" aria-label=\"plugins permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Plugins</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mertkurum/GiderosStoreReview\">SKStoreReview</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mertkurum/GiderosStoreReview\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">0</span></span></a> - Gideros Plugin for SKStoreReviewController iOS 10.3+.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/1025/step-by-step-how-to-write-a-c-plugin-and-deploy-it-to-the-desktop-windows-player\">C++ plugin development</a> - Getting started with Gideros plugin development in C++.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"useful-lua-libraries\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#useful-lua-libraries\" aria-label=\"useful lua libraries permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Useful Lua-Libraries</h2>\n<p><em>General Lua libraries that are useful in gamedev but are not Gideros specific</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rxi/lume\">lume</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rxi/lume\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">574</span></span></a> - Great collection of functions that are useful for game development.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/kikito/inspect.lua\">inspect</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/kikito/inspect.lua\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">888</span></span></a> - Easily pretty-print your tables to the console in a readable way.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://yonaba.github.io/Jumper/\">jumper</a> - Super-fast grid-based pathfinding for Lua.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/kikito/bump.lua\">bump</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/kikito/bump.lua\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">667</span></span></a> - Simple, flexible and fast library for collision detection using axis-aligned bounding boxes (from version 2017.8 onwards Gideros contains a C-port of the library with the same API that should be used instead <a href=\"https://wiki.giderosmobile.com/index.php/Bump\">cbump</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rm-code/Bresenham\">Bresenham</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rm-code/Bresenham\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9</span></span></a> - Bresenham's line algorithm, implemented in Lua.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"related-awesome-lists\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#related-awesome-lists\" aria-label=\"related awesome lists permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Related Awesome Lists</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/LewisJEllis/awesome-lua\">awesome-lua</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/LewisJEllis/awesome-lua\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.7k</span></span></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/love2d-community/awesome-love2d\">awesome-love2d</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https